0British%20Scientist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESir%20Patrick%20Vallance%2C%20the%20UK's%20former%20chief%20scientific%20advisor%2C%20has%20warned%20that%20another%20pandemic%20is%20a%20certainty%20and%20the%20incoming%20government%20needs%20to%20prioritise%20preparedness%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Speaking%20at%20the%20Hay%20Festival%2C%20Vallance%20acknowledged%20the%20upcoming%20election%20but%20stressed%20the%20urgency%20of%20%26quot%3Bsorting%20out%26quot%3B%20critical%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20pressing%20matters%2C%20according%20to%20Vallance%2C%20is%20establishing%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20surveillance%26quot%3B%20to%20detect%20emerging%20threats%20early.%20He%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20rapid%20response%2C%20echoing%20his%20message%20to%20G7%20leaders%20in%202021.%20Vallance%20believes%20readily%20available%20diagnostics%2C%20vaccines%2C%20and%20treatments%20could%20prevent%20the%20need%20for%20drastic%20measures%20witnessed%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20While%20achievable%2C%20these%20improvements%20require%20significant%20international%20%26quot%3Bcoordination%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20cautioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fuk-news%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fmay%2F25%2Fanother-pandemic-is-absolutely-inevitable-says-patrick-vallance-covid%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20he%20said%20that%20by%202023%2C%20the%20G7%20had%20%E2%80%9Csort%20of%20forgotten%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20points%20he%20had%20made%20in%202021.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can't%20forget%20about%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20urged%2C%20recommending%20that%20pandemic%20preparations%20be%20treated%20similarly%20to%20those%20of%20the%20armed%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20we%20have%20to%20have%20an%20army%2C%20not%20because%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20war%20this%20year%2C%20but%20we%20know%20it's%20an%20important%20part%20of%20what%20we%20need%20as%20a%20nation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20treat%20this%20preparedness%20in%20the%20same%20way%20and%20not%20view%20it%20as%20an%20easy%20thing%20to%20keep%20cutting%20back%20when%20there's%20no%20sign%20of%20a%20pandemic%E2%80%94because%20there%20won't%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20pandemic.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHe%20mentioned%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation's%20push%20for%20the%20pandemic%20accord%2C%20a%20proposed%20agreement%20for%20countries%20to%20collaborate%20on%20pandemic%20preparedness%2C%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bpositive%20steps%26quot%3B%20being%20taken.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20I%20don't%20believe%20there%20is%20enough%20focus%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20If%20this%20issue%20is%20removed%20from%20the%20G7%20and%20G20%20agendas%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20will%20be%20in%20the%20same%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20that%20is%20a%20key%20outcome%20of%20the%20inquiry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20problems%20with%20the%20speed%20and%20efficiency%20of%20inquiries%2C%20stating%20that%20we%20%26quot%3Bmust%20find%20a%20better%20way%26quot%3B%20to%20conduct%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Vallance%20believes%20it%20is%20time%20for%20an%20election%2C%20he%20praised%20the%20outgoing%20government's%20anti-smoking%20bill%20and%20expressed%20disappointment%20that%20it%20will%20not%20be%20passed%20before%20the%20election.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20quickly%20afterward%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716875100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fv4npc8b_pnademic_625x300_28_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnext-pandemic-is-absolutely-inevitable-warns-top-british-scientist-5760866%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mr%20Vallance%20endorsed%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation's%20pandemic%20accord%20as%20a%20positive%20step%20but%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20susta