ceX's%20Crew%20Dragon%20spacecraft%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fspacex-crew-dragon-trunk-space-debris-canada%5C%22%3ESpace.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Astronomer%20Jonathon%20McDowell%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fplanet4589%2Fstatus%2F1788675337468911895%5C%22%3E%20added%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20debris%20''definitely%20looks%20consistent%20with%20being%20a%20bit%20of%20the%20Crew-7%20Dragon's%20trunk%20which%20reentered%20on%20a%20path%20right%20over%20this%20location%20on%20Tuesday.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-v-438398f6%3ENotably%2C%20The%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20consists%20of%20two%20main%20parts%3A%20the%20capsule%20and%20the%20trunk.%20The%20trunk%20supports%20the%20spacecraft%20during%20ascent%20and%20carries%20unpressurized%20cargo.%20Typically%2C%20the%20trunk%20burns%20up%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20during%20reentry%2C%20but%20occasionally%2C%20parts%20can%20survive%20and%20fall%20back%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20of%20the%20campsite%20Glamping%20Collective%20said%20that%20they%20plan%20on%20reaching%20out%20to%20aerospace%20experts%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20exactly%20it%20is%20and%20where%20it%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Space%20debris%20was%20not%20on%20our%20list%20of%20things%20we%20expected%20to%20be%20having%20conversations%20about.%20The%20only%20thing%20we've%20been%20able%20to%20come%20up%20with%20is%20that%20it's%20some%20type%20of%20space%20debris%20that%20fell.%20It%20doesn't%20look%20like%20anything%20off%20of%20an%20aeroplane%2C''%20said%20Matt%20Bare%2C%20owner%20of%20The%20Glamping%20Collective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20injuries%20were%20reported%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20suspected%20piece%20of%20space%20junk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716867420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Ftjinr2co_space-object_625x300_28_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworl