et%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665504e2a961b37edf3a2912%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222141%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20German%20cockroach%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20bread.%3Cp%3ESchellhorn%2Fullstein%20bild%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20German%20cockroach%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20household%20pests%20worldwide.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20research%20found%20that%20the%20species%20evolved%20to%20thrive%20in%20human%20dwellings%20about%202%2C100%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20creation%20of%20human-made%20environments%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20researcher%20told%20the%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20ever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-cockroaches-rats-mice-exterminator-places-avoid-infestation-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaw%20a%20cockroach%3C%2Fa%3E%20scuttling%20across%20your%20kitchen%20floor%20or%20a%20restaurant%20wall%2C%20chances%20are%20it%20was%20a%20German%20cockroach.%20The%20German%20roach%20is%20the%20most%20common%20of%20the%2070%20different%20cockroach%20species%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20250%20years%2C%20scientists%20didn't%20know%20where%20it%20came%20from%20and%20how%20it%20managed%20to%20spread%20to%20every%20continent%20on%20Earth%20except%20Antarctica.%20Now%20that%20mystery%20has%20been%20solved%2C%20and%20the%20answer%20is%20that%20it's%20largely%20our%20fault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20cockroach%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20creation%20of%20human-made%20environments%2C%26quot%3B%20Edward%20Vargo%2C%20an%20entomology%20professor%20at%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20University%20and%20co-author%20of%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2401185121%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20identifying%20the%20roach's%20origins%2C%20told%20The%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20cockroach%20can't%20survive%20in%20%26quot%3Btemperate%20winters%20outdoors%26quot%3B%20and%20all%20species%20of%20cockroaches%20%26quot%3Bprefer%20warm%2C%20moist%20places%20where%20they%20can%20feed%20on%20human%20and%20pet%20foods%2C%20decaying%20and%20fermenting%20matter%2C%20and%20a%20variety%20of%20other%20items%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20Illinois%20Department%20of%20Public%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20it's%20pretty%20safe%20to%20say%20that%20if%20human-built%20establishments%20like%20houses%2C%20stores%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20other%20buildings%20didn't%20exist%2C%20neither%20would%20these%20pesky%20pests.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20published%20their%20results%20last%20week%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226fb7a1cb-9f81-4197-9939-0d5b65745e61%5C%22%3EWhere%20did%20the%20German%20roach%20come%20from%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20long%20understood%20that%20the%20species%20thrive%20indoors%2C%20but%20their%20origins%20remained%20a%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20DNA%20analysis%2C%20Vargo%20and%20his%20colleagues%20found%20that%20the%20species'%20closest%20relative%20is%20the%20Asian%20cockroach.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20roach%20evolved%20from%20its%20Asian%20cousin%20about%202%2C100%20years%20ago%20to%20adapt%20to%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20settlements%20in%20India%20or%20Myanmar%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20reported%20in%20their%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20advancements%20in%20transportation%20and%20%26quot%3Btemperature-controlled%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20German%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-get-rid-of-roaches%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecockroach%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20its%20relatively%20recent%20global%20spread%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%20in%20their%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2276a46be3-d8a0-4b80-a863-ddb4fc30ecca%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20German%20cockroach%20took%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20cockroach's%20adaption%20to%20warm%20environments%2C%20ability%20to%20rapidly%20breed%2C%20and%20unique%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-rid-of-cockroachs-2014-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresistance%20to%20insecticides%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20them%20a%20frustratingly%20common%20presence%20in%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20a%20lifetime%2C%20one%20adult%20female%20German%20roach%20can%20produce%20four%20to%20eight%20egg%20capsules%20containing%20up%20to%2048%20eggs%20each%2C%20according%20to%20Penn%20State's%20Department%20of%20Entomology.%20Do%20the%20math%20and%20that's%20between%20192%20to%20384%20roaches%2C%20if%20every%20egg%20survives%20to%20adulthood.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20German%20roaches%20didn't%20migrate%20thousands%20of%20miles%20across%20oceans%20and%20continents%20on%20their%20tiny%20insect%20legs.%20Their%20global%20spread%3Cs%3E%20%3C%2Fs%3Ecoincides%20with%20advancements%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvintage-travel-photos-from-100-years-ago-1920s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20housing%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20the%20researchers%20determined%20that%20the%20German%20cockroach's%20spread%20began%20along%20two%20routes%2C%20west%20and%20east%20of%20its%20origin%20in%20India%20or%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20roach's%20westward%20spread%20likely%20occurred%20during%20times%20of%20increasing%20%26quot%3Bcommercial%20and%20military%20activities%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-10-greatest-empires-in-history-2011-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIslamic%20Umayyad%20or%20Abbasid%20Caliphates%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20about%201%2C200%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20researchers%20reported.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20pest's%20eastward%20spread%20about%20390%20years%20ago%20was%20likely%20caused%20by%20%26quot%3BEuropean%20colonial%20commercial%20activities%20between%20South%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20German%20cockroaches'%20origins%20could%20help%20other%20scientists%20understand%20how%20the%20species%20evolved%20to%20become%20so%20resilient%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcockroaches-becoming-resistant-to-insecticide-harder-to-kill-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommon%20insecticides%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fjee%2Farticle%2F115%2F1%2F259%2F6469283%3Flogin%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20they're%20resistant%20to%20five%20types%20of%20common%20household%20insecticides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20know%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20species%2C%20we%20can%20try%20to%20identify%20the%20mechanism%20of%20this%20rapid%20evolution%20of%20insecticide%20resistance%2C%26quot%3B%20Qian%20Tang%2C%20a%20research%20associate%20at%20Rowland%20Institute%20at%20Harvard%20who%20led%20the%20new%20study%20told%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forigin-cockroaches-evolution-human-made-environments-study-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716854237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66550528239fda2da6cbea9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forigin-cockroaches-evolution-human-made-environments-study-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20German%20cockroach%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20household%20pests%2C%20adapted%20to%20thrive%20in%20human%20dwellings%20about%202%2C100%20years%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engage