e%20years%2C%20I've%20refined%20my%20savings%20strategy.%20Here's%20how%20I%20maximize%20the%20value%20of%20my%20high-yield%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20problem%20with%20one%20savings%20account%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20saving%20in%20my%20early%2020s%2C%20I%20had%20one%20savings%20account.%20I%20wanted%20to%20have%20money%20set%20aside%20for%20emergencies%20or%20anything%20else%20I%20might%20need.%20I%20had%20a%20pot%20of%20cash%20in%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20let's%20say%20several%20thousand%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yet%2C%20each%20month%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20there%20was%20a%20reason%20to%20dip%20into%20my%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20one%20lump%20sum%20of%20cash%20didn't%20give%20me%20any%20clarity%20or%20goals%20for%20how%20I%20should%20use%20the%20money.%20So%20I%20constantly%20found%20reasons%2C%20some%20legitimate%20and%20some%20not%2C%20why%20I%20needed%20to%20tap%20my%20savings.%20I%20finally%20realized%20how%20ineffective%20this%20strategy%20was%20and%20branched%20out%20to%20targeted%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETargeted%20savings%20accounts%20made%20all%20the%20difference%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20my%20bank%20allowed%20me%20to%20open%20up%20to%2025%20different%20savings%20accounts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20nickname%20them.%20I%20decided%20to%20get%20more%20specific%20regarding%20what%20my%20savings%20were%20actually%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20opened%20one%20account%20and%20named%20it%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3EEmergency%20Fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20opened%20another%20account%20and%20named%20it%20%26quot%3BTravel.%26quot%3B%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20created%20a%20%26quot%3BMoving%26quot%3B%20savings%20account%20when%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20from%20Portland%2C%20Oregon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20self-employed%2C%20I%20also%20have%20a%20%26quot%3BBiz%20Taxes%26quot%3B%20savings%20account%2C%20%26quot%3BVacation%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BSick%20as%20a%20Dog%26quot%3B%20funds.%20I%20have%20to%20pay%20my%20own%20taxes%2C%20so%20I%20set%20aside%20more%20than%2030%25%20of%20each%20check%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-pay-quarterly-taxes%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20taxes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20first%20year%20of%20self-employment%2C%20I%20realized%20how%20scary%20it%20was%20to%20get%20sick.%20I%20realized%20I%20felt%20worried%20on%20vacation.%20Why%3F%20Because%20being%20self-employed%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20any%20benefits.%20If%20I%20don't%20work%2C%20I%20don't%20get%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20sick%20or%20on%20vacation%2C%20stressing%20about%20money%20is%20the%20last%20thing%20you%20should%20do.%20So%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20action%20and%20fund%20my%20own%20benefits.%20Having%20a%20buffer%20of%20cash%20in%20case%20anything%20happens%20has%20given%20me%20peace%20of%20mind.%20I%20know%20that%20if%20I%20have%20to%20say%20no%20to%20certain%20assignments%20or%20take%20on%20less%20work%20because%20I'm%20not%20well%20or%20on%20vacation%2C%20I%20can%20do%20so%20and%20still%20pay%20my%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20hyper-specific%20about%20what%20each%20savings%20account%20was%20for%20gave%20me%20clarity%20and%20focus.%20No%20longer%20could%20I%20dip%20into%20these%20accounts%20and%20find%20a%20reason%20to%20use%20the%20funds.%20The%20goal%20was%20clearly%20stated%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20what%20it%20was%20for.%20Having%20separate%20accounts%20and%20naming%20them%20made%20saving%20much%20easier%20for%20me.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20but%20it%20inspired%20me%20because%20I%20knew%20what%20I%20was%20saving%20for%20instead%20of%20just%20saving%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ENext%20Steps%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3EEarn%20up%20to%205.26%25%