th%20the%20Portland%20Trail%20Blazers%20and%20one%20with%20the%20Boston%20Celtics.%20Walton%20was%20the%20NBA's%20MVP%20for%20the%201977%20to%201978%20season.%20Walton%20was%20named%20one%20of%20the%20sport's%20Top%2050%20players%20by%20the%20NBA%20in%201997.%20He%20was%20inducted%20into%20the%20Naismith%20Basketball%20Hall%20of%20Fame%20in%201993%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20College%20Basketball%20Hall%20of%20Fame%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBill%20Walton%20was%20truly%20one%20of%20a%20kind%2C%26quot%3B%20NBA%20Commissioner%20Adam%20Silver%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20Hall%20of%20Fame%20player%2C%20he%20redefined%20the%20center%20position.%20His%20unique%20all-around%20skills%20made%20him%20a%20dominant%20force%20at%20UCLA%20and%20led%20to%20an%20NBA%20regular-season%20and%20Finals%20MVP%2C%20two%20NBA%20championships%2C%20and%20a%20spot%20on%20the%20NBA's%2050th%20and%2075th%20Anniversary%20Teams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20retiring%20from%20basketball%2C%20he%20started%20his%20career%20in%20sports%20broadcasting%20in%201990.%20%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20basketball%20broadcaster%20and%20analyst%2C%20he%20covered%20college%20and%20NBA%20games%20for%20broadcasters%2C%20including%20ESPN%2C%20CBS%2C%20and%20NBC%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20NBA's%20Los%20Angeles%20Clippers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20sports%20commentary%20was%20fun%20and%20colorful.%20Once%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DfDFIzvHg4tE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egobbled%20down%20a%20cupcake%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20topped%20with%20a%20lit%20candle%20on%20live%20TV.%20He%20would%20often%20go%20on%20air%20wearing%20Grateful%20Dead%20t-shirts%20and%20other%20colorful%20attire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Martin%20Jarmond%2C%20UCLA's%20Alice%20and%20Nahum%20Lainer%20Family%20Director%20of%20Athletics%2C%20said%20that%20Walton%20%26quot%3Brepresented%20so%20many%20of%20the%20ideals%20th